      • write

        public AuditLogger.SendStatus write(Calendar timeStamp,
                                    AuditMessage msg)
                             throws IncompatibleConnectionException,
                                    GeneralSecurityException,
                                    IOException
        Send Audit Message by Syslog Protocol to Audit Record Repository, if the message does not match any configured AuditSuppressCriteria. If an I/O error occurs sending the message to the AuditRecordRepository and if a RetryInterval) is configured, the message will be spooled into the configured {@code SpoolDirectory} for later re-send and the method returns {@code false}. If no {@code RetryInterval} is configured, the method throws an {@code IOException) if an I/O error occurs sending the message.

        Attention: sending via UDP without getting an I/O error does not ensure that the Audit Record Repository actually received the message!

        Parameters:
        timeStamp - included in Syslog Header
        msg - Audit Message
        Returns:
        SendStatus.SUPPRESSED if the message was suppressed; SendStatus.SENT if the message was successfully emitted; SendStatus.QUEUED if the message was spooled for later re-send
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if there is no AuditRecordRepository associated with this AuditLogger
        IncompatibleConnectionException - if no Connection) of this {@code AuditLogger} is compatible with any {@code Connection) of the associated {@code AuditRecordRepository}
        GeneralSecurityException - if the SSLContext could not get intialized from configured private key and public certificates
        IOException - if an I/O error occurs sending the message to the AuditRecordRepository or on spooling the message to the file system
